title: ImportError: DLL load failed: The specified module could not be found | lib\site-packages\tensorflow\python\pywrap_tensorflow.py

System information

  • Have I written custom code (as opposed to using a stock example script provided in TensorFlow): No
  • OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04): Win10 x64
  • Mobile device (e.g. iPhone 8, Pixel 2, Samsung Galaxy) if the issue happens on mobile device: -
  • TensorFlow installed from (source or binary): source

  • Bazel version (if compiling from source): -

  • CUDA/cuDNN version: CUDA9 / cuDNN7.0.5
  • GPU model and memory: Nvidia GeForce 1050 Ti

    pip install tensorflow-gpu
    python
    import tensorflow as tf

Describe the problem

I'm trying to install TensorFlow for my study. I tried a few version of python and CUDA/cuDNN but I am still getting the same error. This blog is used to install properly. I have done each steps exactly the same with the blog. I have read and tried solutions from the tensorflow error list and almost all solution provided on the internet. Result is the same.
